questionTemplates.text:
W: Couldn't you walk any faster?
M: This is the fastest I've ever walked.
{a}

M: When did you say the plane would arrive?
W: At a quarter to two.
{a}

W: I've noticed that you spend a lot of time tending your garden. Would you like to join our gardening club? We meet every other Wednesday.
M: Oh, thanks for the invitation, but this is how I relax. I'd rather not make it something formal and structured.
{a}

M: You did a fine job on the room I don't think I've ever seen it so clean.
W: Oh, it's nothing. I'm glad I could help.
{a}

M: Please buy two packs of cigarettes for me while you are at the store.
W: I'm not going to any store. I'm going to see Aunt Mary. But I will get them for you at the gas station.
{a}

M: Let me help you with these bags.
W: Thanks, but it's only ten minutes walk from here to the bus stop.
{a}

M: I'd like to check the present balance in my checking account.
W: As of today you have $2356.8 in your account.
{a}

W: Would you mind if we discuss our plan before dinner?
M: Not at all. I certainly don't want to talk about it over dinner.
{a}

M: Amy, my head is spinning! It must be a touch of the sun.
W: You'd better lie back still for a while. Take it easy for the rest of the day, and stay in the shade. It's too hot today.
{a}

M: I haven't seen Tommy for days.
F: He is in hospital.
{a}

M: If you are in hurry, you can take the subway. If you want to go sightseeing, take a bus.
W: Actually, I don't have to be at the conference before noon.
{a}

M: Here is a concert ticket for you. I hope you will like it.
F: Thanks, Dad!
{a}

W: I'm going to India next month. Is there any advice you'd like to give me on my first trip?
M: Well, see as much as you can, because it's a country with a very different culture from ours.
{a}

M: Jane, I think this meat has gone bad.
W: Yes, we'd better tell the manager about it.
{a}

M: It's ten o'clock and Tom is still in bed.
W: He has caught a bad cold and coughed all night.
{a}

W: The meeting starts at eight thirty.
M: We still have thirty minutes.
{a}

W: Did you tell Mr. Smith to bring the dictionary he promised me?
M: The dictionary? Oh, I am sorry.
{a}

W: How long have you been in this company?
M: I have been here for about 8 years. I came here when I was twenty-one.
{a}

F: Jane is sixteen. How old is her brother?
M: He is two years younger.
{a}

W: How much are those blue plates and bowls?
M: Ten dollars for a set of four-piece.
{a}

M: Would you please tell me where I can get batteries for this brand of camera?
W: Let me have a look. Oh, yes, go down this aisle, pass the garden tools, you'll find them on the shelf next to the light bulbs.
{a}

M: Have you seen Kelly around? We would like to go for lunch.
W: Well, her bag is here on the chair.
{a}

F: Where are Tom and Jim?
M: They have gone to the playground.
{a}

M: I'd like to make two reservations on Flight 651 for June 8th.
W: I'm sorry, we're booked up on the 8th. But we still have a few seats available on the 9th.
{a}

W: Hi, Jack, I just came back yesterday. Anything new while I was away?
M: Congratulations, Susan! It's said you will be promoted to manager and become my immediate boss.
{a}
